Thank you to everyone who joined in today on my very first Divine Feminine Tarot live. I can't believe we are actually here and I'm finally sharing our deck with you, after a year and a half in the making! 

Theo and I are forever grateful that we are able to do this together. I hope you enjoy this deck when it reaches your hands. I poured all the magic I had and so many people worked hard to bring it to life!

Thank you ladies for bringing the dream journal world into reality ♥️ I hope you all have only the sweetest dreams. 🎵 Catching Flies

It has been almost a month since I held my very first deck for the first time. It took a long long journey to shed my skin and old habits in order to discover who I really am, who I’m meant to be in this life and what I’m meant to do 
And this is it. My dream has always been creating magic. It’s has always been my safe place, the spark that lives in my chest and fills me in with breath and passion

It never gets old feeling the excitement of having their magic in my hands and even more seeing how much you have been loving them. In the video, appear both the gold and holographic gold foil silk cloths 🎵 Diomede by Undroid

Let’s get spooked together, share the craziest, most terrifying experiences in the comments. I promise I to lose my sleep forever 😅

node.text:
I recently read about the R.A.I.N. method for kids feeling overwhelmed with too many emotions to handle. May I say that it works perfectly for grown-ups too? On rainy AND sunny days (although I prefer rainy ones, please 🙋🏼‍♀️)

R. Recognize
A. Accept
I. Investigate
N. Non-identify 

R. Take a step back and observe the emotions or thoughts which are paining you. First, name the emotions that you are feeling, perhaps “annoyance,” “overloaded with work,” or “didn’t like how I reacted.” These emotions should be treated without judgment as good or bad.

A. Recognize that the difficult emotion you’re experiencing right now is your reality. They should not be pushed under the surface of your consciousness, left to fester there until they unsurface in an unwelcome moment. Instead, put these emotions front and center in your mind and say “yes, this is how I’m feeling,” without attempting to change it.

I. Try to approach your thoughts with an attitude of curiousness and ask yourself questions about the emotions you’ve been carrying: how did this start? Have I felt this way before? This should help you identify the other elements of the emotion besides the main negative feeling.

N. When you have a negative emotion, you can feel like it’s the only part of you that matters at that time. Non-identification means that you should acknowledge that you are a whole person, and this difficult emotion is just a tiny, fleeting part of who you are. Simply see the negative thoughts scrolling past you, mainly caused by outside forces, and detach yourself from them.

RAIN is a process that Michelle McDonald developed as part of the mindfulness movement, and @tarabrach

Massive, heavy, hardcover, synthetic leather and gold foil, and the most precious, handmade paper inside - to hold and protect your magic, forever.

Our very first oracle deck is now officially available for pre-order 🦌 Cosmic Wild Oracle Deck [Pre-order] ✨ I have so much love for this one; working with these animals for this deck has fought me so much the past months. It’s been a true blessing!

So many of our things went out for pre-order today; this deck, the new 2022 Aurele planner, and our collection of Grimoires 🥰
